HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 8
By Clemmons
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of James Ralph Sasser.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of James Ralph Sasser, former United States Senator for the State of Tennessee;
and
WHEREAS, Senator Jim Sasser was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in Memphis in 1936, James Ralph Sasser attended the University of
Tennessee and graduated from Vanderbilt University in 1958 before receiving his law degree
from Vanderbilt University Law School in 1961; and
WHEREAS, Senator Sasser began his lifetime of service to the United States as a
member of the United States Marine Corps Reserve from 1957 to 1963; and
WHEREAS, upon graduation from law school, he joined the Nashville legal firm of
Goodpasture, Carpenter, Woods and Sasser, where he remained a partner until 1972; and
WHEREAS, having been bitten by the political bug after working on political campaigns
early in his career, Senator Sasser served as the Chairman of the Tennessee Democratic Party;
and
WHEREAS, in 1976, Jim Sasser was elected to the United States Senate, where he
served with distinction for three terms, which included a tenure as chairman of the Committee
on the Budget of the Senate that saw him help negotiate and pass budget deals under
presidents George H. W. Bush and Bill Clinton; and
